      <title>Re: Guild Question??</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=240346#M240346</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;guild hall features / benefits:&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;1- buff timers are frozen.&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp; Get buffed in the GH and the timers won't start counting down till you leave.&amp;nbsp; Esp. useful if you need to afk but not necessarily&amp;nbsp;log off, and have the time to park yourself there (as opposed to emergency/unexpected afks)&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;2-Meditation pool.&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp; Sit in the pool and your mana and HPs will regen at double the rate.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;4. Portal.&lt;/STRONG&gt; Buy a port stone from the gnome and hand it back to him, and you can port to a few different destinations.&amp;nbsp; The great thing is multiple people can use the portal to go to the same destination, and only need to buy another port stone when a new destination is required...thus useful to move an entire raid...&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;5. Tradeskill containers.&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp; IS poK too crowded or distracting? Sit in the nice quiet guild hall to do your combines.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;6. Augmentation sealer.&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp; (birdbath) Add augments to your gear, or remove them&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;7. NPC merchant.&lt;/STRONG&gt; Sells food &amp;amp; water and augmentation removal potions, and will buy your vendor loot if you forgot to unload before you zoned in.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;8. Personal banker.&lt;/STRONG&gt; convenient, esp if you think ahead and fill it with your tradeskill components so you dont need to zone out to PoK :)&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;9. Guild Banker.&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp; useful for guilds to share gear, tradeskill &amp;amp; quest items&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;10. Guild Tribute person.&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp; tribute effects for teh whole guild, you must right click and tick teh "opt in" box in order to get any benefit from the effects.&amp;nbsp; Also can donate to this NPC (most convenient for guild bankers unloading raid loot, they don't have to zone out to PoK and climb the tower where the other Guild Tribute NPC is located).&amp;nbsp; NOTE: only the leader or a guild officer can turn Guild Tribute on or off, which generally means it's reserved for use on raids....&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;11. Future features?&lt;/STRONG&gt; there are doors that lead nowhere at the moment, many suggestions have been made....maybe one day we will see one or more implemented...&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Corpse Summoning Altar&lt;/STRONG&gt; is in the &lt;U&gt;Guild Lobby.&lt;/U&gt;&amp;nbsp; Buy the soulstone that corresponds to your level, give it to a summoner NPC and your body will be summoned from anywhere in Norrath (except Shadowrest if your corpse was too old and was sent there.&amp;nbsp; Then all you need is a cleric to rez you (usually is at least one cleric in the lobby willing to rez for donations...)&lt;/P&gt;</description>
