    <item>
      <title>Re: Guild Question??</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=240323#M240323</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;Tonad918 wrote:&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;I guess what I'm confused about is WHY would I contribute to the Guild Bank/Guild Tribute and WHAT benefits do I get from doing so? Thanks again.&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Well, why would you use the guild bank?  Let's say that you are a young member of the guild and some of the higher ups are out adventuring and they get some gear to drop.  It is really nothing they would use but they figure that the guild might have people that could use it.  So rather than selling it in the bazaar to make a little money or donate it to their personal tribute master in their hometown, they donate it to the guild bank. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now one day you are starting to feel like your armor is getting to be just a little under where you feel it should be.  I mean, that 20AC Netherbian Chitin was good for a while but you are getting older now and have been looking at upgrading.  You look in the guildbank and see that there is a nice Dented Brass Cuirass that is AC30 and has some ok stats to go with it that a guildy put in for someone to use.  It is certainly an upgrade, and you would like it.  In some guilds it might be setup for anyone to take if they can use it and you simply withdraw it.  In other others you might have to use points earned by doing things with the guild to buy it from the guild with points or you might simply have to post your desire to get it on a guild website so that someone with the proper ability to get it out could get it and give it to ya.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now that Netherbian Chitin you are upgrading from are a dime a dozen and you can buy them on vendors for 5p all the time so you likely won't make any real money from it in the bazaar and most people in guild probably won't need it so you can turn it in for guild tribute if you like and everyone in the guild gets to use the abilities setup by those who can do such things with the tribute master.  You could also turn it into your own Tribute Master in your hometown.  If you turn it in to the guild tribute master, you are helping all of the guild keep the tribute benefits going that much longer.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Being in a guild is usually about helping each other and should be.  As a guildy with a high fletching skill I expect to make combines for free or if I need to buy things I expect to simply be re-imbursed for materials whereas normal people would get a markup or sometimes pay a fee to get the combine done.  Guild banks and tribute are no different.  They are ways of helping the guild and in turn, helping yourself.  At the upper levels, maybe it means turning Muramite Runes into the Guild Bank so others can get their spells rather than selling them and making some money for example.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
