    <item>
      <title>Re: Guild Question??</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=240214#M240214</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The guild leader will assign 1+ members to be guild bankers.  If you deposit somethiing to guildbank, usualy that means you are donating it for anyone in guild to use.  If you want the item to go to a specific person only, you need to tell the banker ahead of time so they can set the proper removal rights (public access, public if usable-for class specific things, single person-they type in a name, banker access only).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I don't know about all guilds, but the ones I've seen have frowned upon someone using guildbank as additional bank space for themselves, so if I misunderstood what you said about taking something back out I apologize.  Yes, a banker can assign the single person name to the person who put it in or can put public access on something and you can remove it that way.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Regarding tribute.  There are 2 forms of tribute - personal tribute (that you, yourself, can only donate to and you have to set your tribute rights of what you want in your home town) and then there is guild tribute.  There is a cap of 250,000 tribute I believe that a person can have as single personal tribute.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Guilds have the eoption to allow their members to gain additional mana, hp, resists, etc. by the guild tribute (the person in guild hall as well as in the top of one of the spires).  However, to participate in this, you have to go to them and turn yourself on for guild tribute, so that when it is running, you feel the benefits - just because guild tribute is running, if you haven't turned yourself on, you won't get the benefits.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Raid tribute costs are NOT cheap (and there is a 500,000 cap on guild tribute) because for every person who joins in, the price goes up; there is no flat fee for 1-100 raiders being on at a time.  So donating to is is beneficial, and especially if you use it during raids yourself.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
